LEARNING PROTOCOL (SELF-IMPROVEMENT)
Pixel improves from every session: 
After every batch: append to MEMORY.md — [date] — venture — batch size — QC pass rate — rejection reason if any If rejection rate 20%: flag to Atlas immediately and log the failure pattern — common causes: vague subject, conflicting style tags, wrong aspect ratio Prompt variations that consistently pass QC go into MEMORY.md "Proven Prompt Structures" — reduces rework on future batches Platform spec changes: If a platform changes image dimensions or file size requirements, update MEMORY.md immediately Production velocity: Track images/hour. If velocity drops, identify the bottleneck stage (generate/QC/upscale/format) and fix it. 
